# Home IDS lab

## Overview
Built a Home SOC Lab using:
- Windows victim machine
- Linux server running Suricata
- Linux server running Splunk

## Architecture
Laptop A (
│
├── Splunk Enterprise
├── Splunk MLTK
├── Python AI Triage
└── Splunk Web UI

Laptop B
VM 1: Kali Linux
├── Suricata IDS/IPS
└── Splunk Universal Forwarder

VM 2: Windows 10/11
├── Victim Machine
└── Sysmon

## Tools Used
- Suricata
- Splunk
- Sysmon

## Challenges
The major challenge i faced was sending sysmon logs to the splunk. Splunk universal forwader and splunk reciver were working fine.
But still i was not reciving logs.The issue that i identified was that the inputs file was not confiured correcly.

