## Key Learnings
Gained hands-on experience in building a basic SOC (Security Operations Center) environment using real security tools and virtual machines.
Understood how network traffic monitoring and intrusion detection works using Suricata in IDS/IPS mode.
Learned how a SIEM system (Splunk) collects, indexes, and analyzes security logs for threat detection.
Improved understanding of endpoint telemetry and Windows event logging using Sysmon.
Faced and resolved challenges in log forwarding from Windows to Splunk, improving troubleshooting skills in agent configuration and data ingestion.
Learned how different security components (endpoint, network, SIEM) work together in a centralized security monitoring workflow.
Developed practical skills in log analysis, alert investigation, and security event correlation.
